<subSubSection pageId="434" pageNumber="435" type="diversity">
<paragraph pageId="434" pageNumber="435">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="434" pageNumber="435">
New World, with about 125 species arrayed in seven genera: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Paulsen &amp; Smith" authorityYear="2003" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Erwiniana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="434" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="434" pageNumber="435">Erwiniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Paulsen and Smith (about 55 Neotropical species), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Erwin" authorityYear="1994" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Geballusa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="434" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="434" pageNumber="435">Geballusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Erwin (five Neotropical species), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Erwin" authorityYear="1994" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Gouleta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="434" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="434" pageNumber="435">Gouleta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Erwin (four Neotropical species), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Erwin" authorityYear="1978" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Inpa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="434" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="434" pageNumber="435">Inpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Erwin (one South American species), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1882" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Mioptachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="434" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="434" pageNumber="435">Mioptachys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(13 species), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Erwin" authorityYear="1994" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Philipis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="434" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="434" pageNumber="435">Philipis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Erwin (38 Australian species), and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schaum" authorityYear="1863" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Xystosomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="434" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="434" pageNumber="435">Xystosomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Schaum (nine Neotropical species). The North American fauna is represented by a single species.
</paragraph>
